{
  "doc_id": "16316",
  "text": "CINC1 is produced by astrocytes in response to various noxious stimuli, including oxidative stress [CITATION_1] . Elevated serum levels of fibrinogen, a plasma glycoprotein, are another indication of altered microcirculation and inflammation; increased levels of fibrinogen can increase blood viscosity as well as vascular permeability [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . According to studies showing correlation between elevated fibrinogen precursor protein and Alzheimer's disease, elevated fibrinogen levels can link inflammation and vascular damage to neurodegeneration. MIP1α is a proinflammatory chemokine, and its elevated serum levels are yet another indicator of inflammation [CITATION_4] .",
